Determining the sounds to imitate

We started with 6 sounds in each of 6 categories and reduced that number to 4 sounds in each of 4 categories through two “odd one out” norming experiments.

Collecting iterated imitations

Matching imitations to original sounds

Collecting transcriptions of sounds

Methods

Selected messages

We selected 16 messages to transcribe: 2 of the 4 seed sound effects used in each category of sounds, and 2 messages selected by hand from later generations in each chain.

Results

There was less agreement among transcribers for the seed sound effects than there was among the transcribers of n-th generation imitations.
